description:
Support per-dataset configuration for events:

```json
{
  "events": true,
  "compaction": { "interval": "1h", "retention": "30d" }
}
```

- events: false (default) = read-only snapshot mode (simple datasets like IMDB)
- events: true = mutable with history, time-travel enabled
- Wire config into write path to emit events
- Wire config into read path to support { at: timestamp }

File: src/config/dataset.ts

All errors are thrown rather than returned. Implement functional error handling:

type Result<T, E = Error> = { ok: true; value: T } | { ok: false; error: E }

Replace throw-based patterns in critical paths with Result returns for better type safety.
